    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>mayo </strong>and<strong> remaining grated</strong> <strong>garlic </strong>(not a fan of raw garlic? Just add a little!) in a bowl with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>cold water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong> – this is your <strong>garlic mayo</strong></p><p>Wash your<strong> lettuce[s]</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper and shred finely</p><p>Chop your <strong>tomato[es] </strong>finely</p><p>Chop your <strong>cucumber</strong> into quarters lengthways, then chop roughly</p>",
